was anyone else a mover during labor tonight at our birthing class we practiced different pain coping techniques while holding ice in our hand for one minute to simulate a contraction everyone else in the class closed their eyes breathed slowly and went to their happy place while the instructor played snorah jones on the cd player not me i had to keep tapping my feet or counting or bopping up and down on the birth ball or i couldn't handle it and the song i really wanted to hear was metallica's fuel did anyone else need heavy metal and constant movement to get through labor any advice based on your experience i can imagine i will get really tired but i just can't do the mushy yoga find your inner child junk i would like to see someone actually relax and go to their happy place during labor birthing classes just want you to believe it will be all roses when you go to deliver it isn't called labor for nothing i am sure there are those few who get so much pain meds that they don't feel anything and labor is a walk in the park but realistically it doesn't happen that way for most my brother's girlfriend had so much meds that she fell asleep and they had to wake her up and tell her to push with my first i had too many meds and didn't feel a thing until it was time to have stitches with my next meds wore off halfway through and they wouldn't give me anymore so i resorted to my own form of pain control and i screamed loud people on other floors heard me Shaggy dog story Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Childbirth Urinary incontinence Massage Tai Chi Chuan Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Prank flash Philosophical skepticism Out-of-body experience Diving Kodocha The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Jon Secada Tag Mattress Aerial (dance move) EastEnders Blood on the Tracks Avenue Q Wonderland (McFly album) Lucid dreaming Naruto jutsu The Shining (film) Characters of Naruto Salad Fingers 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Escape from New York Aikido Fecal incontinence 